cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about improving the performance of single stage object detectors, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves optimizing the model in a consistent way, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The authors also discuss the behavior of the detector and how it affects performance, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper focuses on object detection, which is a common task in robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the authors evaluate their method on the COCO dataset, which is a popular benchmark in multimedia (cs.MM).
